cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.GR 

This paper deals with the problem of crosswalk classification using deep learning models trained on large-scale satellite imagery data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of crowdsourcing systems for data acquisition and annotation, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of deep learning models for classification is also related to cs.LG (Machine Learning), and the use of satellite imagery data involves the processing of large-scale data, which is related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.GR (Graphics).
